introduction: American actor Brett Davis is popularly known for his role as Mitch in the American drama series, The Haves And The Have Nots.Born and raised on a farm in Maryland, Brett is the oldest of three siblings. After graduation, he moved to New York City from Maryland to pursue his career in acting. It was in New York where Brett was introduced to the entertainment world.In New York, Brett first started modeling, working consistently for department store catalogs to fitness modeling and runway. Later on, these credits opportunities helped him landing on his first job on the big screen. He got his first television role via the hit soap opera, All My Children.After that, he also made his appearance on other couples of roles in New York before moving to Los Angeles for bigger and better opportunities.In Los Angeles, he jumped right into the commercial scene, booking national commercials for Kia, Hyundai, Papa Johns, Scope and Doritos.Besides that, Brett was also able to score roles in music videos for Avril Lavigne, Brittany Spears (Femme Fatale Tour) and Aubrey O'Day.As per wiki, he also has some television roles on his credits such as Hollywood Heights, The Young and Restless, and his most recent and proud accomplishment, the role of Mitch on Tyler Perry's hit show, The Haves, and The Have Nots.
